<pre class="bz_comment_text">Comment on <span class=""><a href="attachment.cgi?id=203580" name="attach_203580" title="patch to make connections fail if ssl-strict is set but no ssl-ca-file is used">attachment 203580</a> <a href="attachment.cgi?id=203580&amp;action=edit" title="patch to make connections fail if ssl-strict is set but no ssl-ca-file is used">[details]</a></span> <a href="review?bug=666280&amp;attachment=203580">[review]</a>
patch to make connections fail if ssl-strict is set but no ssl-ca-file is used

This is a documentation problem then; changing the behavior would be an ABI break.

FWIW, in libsoup 2.38, there will be a property you can set on SoupSession to make it use "sane" defaults rather than backwards-compatible ones. (<a href="http://git.mysterion.org/libsoup/commit/?h=features&amp;id=0c8f8dd83a30d236a2c9a7bd4988ba90da1358c4">http://git.mysterion.org/libsoup/commit/?h=features&amp;id=0c8f8dd83a30d236a2c9a7bd4988ba90da1358c4</a>)</pre>
