<pre class="bz_comment_text">Thanks for your quick reply (and also for your reply to #666276). The new option to enable better defaults looks very good indeed.

Given these new options I wonder if there is a plan to to release a 3.0 version that breaks the backward-compatiblity at some point in the future? Or maybe even just break compatibility for the security defaults? Among other things having those defaults is nice for users who may not even be aware that they are using libsoup underneath (like e.g. python-webkit users).</pre>
</div><div class="bz_comment" id="c3">
