        </span>
</div>
<pre class="bz_comment_text">The problem here is just that "ssl-strict" is a bad name. It probably
should have been "ssl-unstrict" (with the meanings of TRUE/FALSE
reversed). But anyway, the point is that ssl-strict == TRUE doesn't
really mean "be strict", it means "behave exactly like libsoup always
behaved up until 2.30". And before 2.30, if ssl-ca-file was set, then
it was was strict, and if ssl-ca-file wasn't set, then any certificate
was accepted. So that's what ssl-strict==TRUE has to mean.

I've updated the documentation a bit to clarify.</pre>
